.TH "srp_build_response" 9 "srp_build_response" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
srp_build_response \- Build an SRP response buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "long" srp_build_response
.BI "(struct scsi_info *vscsi "  ","
.BI "struct ibmvscsis_cmd *cmd "  ","
.BI "uint *len_p "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vscsi" 12
Pointer to our adapter structure
.IP "cmd" 12
Pointer to command for which to send the response
.IP "len_p" 12
Where to return the length of the IU response sent.  This
is needed to construct the CRQ response.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Build the SRP response buffer and copy it to the client's memory space.
